Institute, 1985), p. 388.
<P>
<P><TT><B><A NAME="7">7</A></B></TT> After the first $20 million in 
revenue, only 1 percent may be applied to advocacy activities. For example, an organization 
with nongrant revenues of $30 million would be limited to $1,100,000 in lobbying 
expenditures ($1,000,000 plus $100,000).
