<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Heritage Foundations Foreign Policy and Defense Studies Department
</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<center><IMG SRC="/heritage/thf_log2.gif"></a></center>
<P>
<H2>The Heritage Foundation's Foreign Policy and Defense Studies
Department</H2>
<HR>
<P>
The department conducts research and publishes papers on a wide
variety of international political, economic, and security issues.
Because its primary audience is the U.S. Congress, it convenes
working groups; organizes lectures, debates and luncheon talks;
and conducts briefings on timely foreign policy and defense issues
for congressmen and their staffs. Heritage staffers also give
interviews and conduct briefings for radio, television, and newspaper
reporters. 
<P>
Recent major projects include: the publication of the <A
HREF="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/econ_index/toc.html.cgi"<I>Index
of Economic Freedom</A></I>, a quantitative analysis and ranking
of economic freedom in over 100 countries which will be used to
form a new approach to U.S. foreign aid based on free market economic
principles; the publication of  <a href="/townhall/townhall_shop/safe.html">A Safe and Prosperous America</a>,
Heritage's blueprint for future U.S. defense and foreign policy;
and the forthcoming publication of  <I>Defending America: A Near-and-Long
Term Plan to Deploy Missile Defenses </I>, which advocates the
rapid development and deployment of effective missile defenses.
Heritage staffers were instrumental in developing the defense
and foreign policy agenda items in the House Republican &quot;Contract
with America.&quot; Other high priority items include the  Asian
Studies Center , which analyzes political, economic, and security
issues relevant to U.S. policy in Asia; the Russian Reform project,
which seeks to aid the development of democracy and capitalism
in Russia; and the America Trader Initiative, which seeks to promote
global  free trade . 
<p>
<a href="/townhall/townhall_shop/thpubs.html">To Order Heritage Foundation
Publications</a>
